(118 App. Div. 897) QUINLAN v. CITY OF NEW YORK. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, Second Department. March 1, 1907.) Appeal from Trial Term, Kings County. Action by Annie L,. Quinlan against the city of New York. Judgment for plaintiff, and defendant appeals. Affirmed.

Argued before JENKS, HOOKER, GAYNOR, and MILLER, JJ.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment unanimously affirmed, with costs, on the authority of Gravey v. City of New York (decided herewith) 102 N. Y. Supp. 1010.
